<html>
	<head>
		<meta name="keywords" content="Debug, Console, Run statements" />
		<title>Console Window</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="normal.css" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>Console Window</h1>
		<img src="img/ConsoleForm.png" align="left" hspace="20" vspace="10" />
		<p>In this window you can watch the debug output log from your code. You can write to the debug output from your code by calling
			<code>Debug.Write</code> and <code>Debug.WriteLine</code>. Below the debug output you can write C# statements and execute them by
			pressing the 
			<img alt="Run" src="img/Icons.Run.png" style="vertical-align: middle" /> button.
		</p>
		<h3>Toolbar</h3>
		<p>
			With the <img alt="Close" src="" style="vertical-align: middle" src="img/delete.gif" /> <b>Close</b> button you close the Console window.<br />
				With the <img alt="Run" style="vertical-align: middle" src="img/Icons.Run.png" /> <b>Run</b> button you execute the C# command in the bottom textbox.<br />
				With the <img alt="Clear" style="vertical-align: middle" src="img/Icons.Trash.png"/> <b>Clear</b> button you clear the top output textbox.<br />
				With the <img alt="Help" style="vertical-align: middle" src="img/Icons.MenuHelpHelpTopicsIcon.png" /> <b>Help</b> button you show this text.<br />
				With the <img alt="Help on Library" style="vertical-align: middle" src="img/Icons.MenuHelpTutorialsIcon.png"/> <b>Library help</b> button you display help about the JohnsHope.FPlot.Library
				namespace.
		</p>		
	</body>
</html>